element.name: River Dodder by toczygroszek, Unknown Cache (3.5/1)
element.long-description:
The River Dodder (Irish: An Dothra) is one of the three main rivers in Dublin. It begins on the northern slopes of Kippure in the Wicklow Mts. and is more than 20 km long.
The coordinates above are for reference only. For the real coordinates you must solve the puzzle below:
You can check your answers for this puzzle on
Geochecker.com.
Don't forget to take a note of the information on the lid which is important to find the River Liffey cache.

RD1JRXC - The Cache

element.encoded-hints: it looks fishy, isn't? Catch all fish and gut while looking for the key.
